summary: My personal upbringing, past employment and educational background have afforded me the unique experiences that make me who I am today and an exceptional asset to the Intelligence, law enforcement and security fields. Being born and raised in Dhahran, Saudi Arabia and having lived in the Kingdom for 19 years has enabled me to learn how those in the Middle East differ and how those cultural differences can affect overall understanding of foreigners and life abroad. I have had the opportunity to travel the world including countries throughout Europe, Africa and the Middle East. I believe this life experience has allowed me to see the bigger world picture and take from it, aspects that I can use to solve or understand real world issues and challenges. My previous employment includes positions in the law enforcement and security fields. These professional experiences have given me exposure to high-pressure environments where attention to detail, multitasking and interpersonal communication was essential in performing my duties. I frequently conducted thorough investigations and drafted detailed and concise reports in order to communicate effectively with both internal and external audiences, as major decisions were often based from my findings. My extensive knowledge of the national security, intelligence and counterintelligence disciplines was gained through obtaining a Master's degree from the Institute of World Politics in Washington, DC. During that time I authored analytical reports, both independently and in teams, on a variety of subjects concerning national security topics. Such topics included; issues in current foreign affairs, strategic intelligence and analysis techniques, counterintelligence challenges and historical case studies in intelligence operations. I hope to enter into the fields of National Security, intelligence, security, law enforcement, working directly to support Intelligence collection, analysis or counterintelligence.Specialties:Intelligence, Counterintelligence, Law Enforcement and Security

summary: I am a very down-to-earth, hard-working, professional individual with career-driven goals, an upbeat personality, and a knack for numbers. After growing up on my parents' 550+ acre Beef and Grain farm, I developed a passion for Agriculture, and a curiosity in the financial realm behind it. It is this curiosity that led me to pursue a career in Business and Accounting. To start off my college career, I attended UW-Whitewater from 2011-2014, double-majoring in Accounting and Finance. After recently transferring to Marian University in Fond Du Lac, Wisconsin, I am in my 4th year as an Accounting major working towards my Bachelor of Science in Business Administration. I will be graduating in December of 2015. My ultimate career goal is to specialize in Agricultural Accounting and Financial Analyzing, but my current interests include Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable, Corporate Tax, and Audit. I am, however, extremely open to experience any and all opportunities that would allow me to expand my current skill-set and knowledge beyond these areas.

summary: We’ve heard the horror stories. Your favorite watch breaks, just as the warranty has run out. You take it to a department store, and after waiting for as long as a month, you get quoted an exorbitant price that’s way more than you expected. When you ask why, you’re given the ambiguous response that, on top of your requested repairs, the watch also needed additional and unspecified “service.” You get upset, you may even try to negotiate, but in the end, what else can you do? You either pay the price, or throw the watch in the garbage. At Watch Repair & Co., these types of stories make us upset. Really upset. That’s why our #1 goal is to provide speedy service at a price that won’t make your heart race. Maybe you have a watch you cherish that constantly needs repair. Maybe you just bought an incredible watch that just needs service for the first time. But just because your watch is special does not give watchmakers an excuse to rip you off. Our customers get the lowest prices and experience the highest expectations. Our jewelers and watchmakers are experts at their craft, with years of experience to draw from. Our team of expert watchmakers repairs and services almost everything: watches, jewelry, cutlery, and more. They also do engraving and polishing at a fraction of what the other guys will charge. Service is our business model. It’s the main reason we’ve been so busy and successful in this brutal economy. For us, premium service is going above and beyond to make every customer happy. We offer the highest quality skill and craftsmanship, backed by years of experience, done in a workshop full of the latest tools and technology, at a price that will make you happy. We guarantee that your watch or piece gets the VIP treatment, every time. Anything less…well, that’s just not Watch Repair & Co.

description: • Created and perfected several unique analytic methods to quickly search up to 50,000 unique selectors over 700+ information streams at least 600% faster than previous methods. • Pioneered multiple analytic concepts which discovered links within large data repositories, which enabled previously impossible link analysis. • Crafted complex query constructs capturing 100% of relevant traffic with less than a 10% false hit rate. • Worked with management team to identify, quantify and pursue business leads at five clients, resulting in an additional $300,000+ in revenue annually over the last three years. • Identified and pursued innovative solutions at a client to add additional 10% to revenue annually for last three years. • Created innovative means of gaining corporate access to previously unavailable potential clients, resulting in eight additional leads, and two additional contracts with over $600,000 in total revenue. • Proven record of customer satisfaction, 100% of contracts renewed at the same or higher rates. • Provides specialized intelligence support to Law Enforcement enabling field elements to access previously unseen information, resulting in precise targeting of networks. • Identified an innovative solution at a client to add additional 10% to revenue annually over three years. • Gathered, deconflicted, provided justifications, and submitted over 100 requirements into the development backlog, resulting in 15 requirements selected for development. • Supervised the contracts at three different clients, including two simultaneously, resulting in contracts at all three clients managed to within 3% of total value annually. • Technical liaison at a large IT contract, providing the client and stakeholders with realistic expectations, and timelines for completion of their requirements. • Recognized as a mentor and leader within organization. Successfully trained and mentored a failing team member to a Team Lead position.

summary: Current TOP SECRET/SCI Clearance with CI POLY (DIA 1991). 30 plus years of active military service as a career professional U.S. NAVY Intelligence Officer and GG14 (0132). I have acquired extensive knowledge to include recent “boots on the ground” field experience in a combat environment in Iraq (2010) as a Government Civilian (GS) Defense Contractor in support of OPERATION IRAQI FREEDOM (OIF) and as a Defense Contractor on two Afghanistan (2011-12) study groups in support of OPERATION ENDURING FREEDOM (OEF).Senior All-Source Intelligence Analyst having worked at the Joint IED Defeat Organization (JIEDDO) in support of OIF and at the National Ground Intelligence Center (NGIC) in support of OEF as a Senior Principal Intelligence Analyst responsible for the Supervision, Development and Production of Strategic Intelligence Analysis activities consistent with NGIC requirements. Familiar with COIC (A3P) course.Graduate (1982) of the Air Force targeting school.Created and briefed intelligence products (for PACOM/LANTCOM J2 staffs) multiple-sources (HUMINT, SIGINT, IMINT, MASINT). Completion of Counter IED Operations/Intelligence Integration Center Attack the Network (AtN) and Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures (TTPs); key leadership; and logistical support networks in Iraq and Afghanistan in support of NATO/ISAF and US Counter Improvised Explosive Device (C-IED), Counter Terrorism (CT), Special skills officer, Force Protection (FP), and Counter Insurgency (COIN) operations, focused on Asymmetric Warfare, MISO, Irregular Warfare and F3EA. Have experience developing Time-Phased Force Deployment Data (TPFDD). Performed weaponeering and Collateral Damage Estimates (CDE). Intelligence tools and applications, to include the Web Intelligence Search Engine (WISE), TAC, Analyst Notebook 8, HUMINT, HOT-R, Palantir, BIARS, BIAR, and TIDE. GG14 for DoD M&S at MTWS and AWSIM. Senior Targets/CENTCOM

summary: I am seeking employment in national security utilizing my skills, experiences, and interests, such as the intelligence community, aviation operations, policy and oversight, or more. Washington, DC is my preferred home base. I served on active duty in the US Navy as a pilot for ten years (1996 to 2006), and continue to serve as a pilot in the Navy Reserve. I currently fly C-130 Hercules transport aircraft as a Navy Reservist. I have nearly 3,000 flight hours flying C-130s, C-26 Metroliners, H-60 Seahawk helicopters, and H-1 Huey helicopters. I am particularly interested in flying UAVs (Unmanned Aerial Vehicles) or RPVs (Remotely Piloted Vehicles). I also have experience with Naval Intelligence and the Navy Staff at the Pentagon (OPNAV N3/N5) and have been stationed in the US and Japan. I am also a graduate of the Johns Hopkins University School of Advanced International Studies (SAIS), Embry-Riddle Aeronautical University, and the University of Texas at Austin. I am a US citizen and maintain an active security TS/SCI clearance with a CI polygraph. Specialties: Military Intelligence, Chinese language ability (Mandarin), aviation operations.
